# Motion Animation — Spring & Performance

Use **[Motion for React](https://motion.dev/docs/react)** (`motion` package) with **spring** transitions. Keep Chrome main-thread light; scrolling must stay smooth.

## Setup (required)

| Rule | Detail |
|------|--------|
| Provider | `MotionProvider` in `main.tsx` — `LazyMotion` + `domAnimation` + `strict` |
| Component | `m` from `motion/react-m` — **never** import full `motion` |
| Presets | `springSnappy`, `springGentle`, `viewportOnce` from `src/lib/motion.ts` |
| Reduced motion | `usePrefersReducedMotion()` — skip animation, render static |

## Animation tiers

| Tier | Routes / usage | Behavior |
|------|----------------|----------|
| `full` | `/` landing | `FadeInView`, `StaggerChildren` on sections & card grids |
| `lite` | `/kursus`, `/pmb`, `/admin` | `PageEnter` fade on route mount via `AnimatedOutlet` |
| `none` | Forms, tables, `/admin/login`, `/pmb/daftar` | No Motion wrappers on data-heavy UI |

Route tier logic lives in [`AnimatedOutlet.tsx`](../../frontend/src/components/motion/AnimatedOutlet.tsx).

## Allowed properties

Animate **only** compositor-friendly properties:

- `opacity`
- `transform` (`x`, `y`, `scale`)

## Forbidden

- `layout` prop, `domMax`, drag/pan gestures
- `useScroll` parallax or scroll event listeners for animation
- Animating `width`, `height`, `top`, `left`, `margin`, `padding`
- Motion on admin tables (`AdminPaginatedTable`), forms, skeleton loaders
- Replacing Radix/shadcn CSS enter/exit (Sheet, Dialog, Accordion)

## Components

| Component | Use |
|-----------|-----|
| `FadeInView` | Scroll reveal (`whileInView`, `once`) |
| `StaggerChildren` + `StaggerItem` | Card grids on landing |
| `PageEnter` | Route mount fade (`lite` tier) |
| `MotionTierProvider` | Pass tier to descendants |

## Example

```tsx
import { FadeInView, StaggerChildren, StaggerItem } from '@/components/motion'

<StaggerChildren className="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
  {items.map((item) => (
    <StaggerItem key={item.id}>
      <Card>...</Card>
    </StaggerItem>
  ))}
</StaggerChildren>
```

